  "texts": [
    "We compare the ground truth (top row) with our surrogate (second row) and the ablations (third and fourth row).Figure 9 shows that, for ξ = ξ 2, the original ABM also converges toward a segregated state, but the convergence occurs more slowly than in the ξ 1 case.",
    "The resulting clusters are larger and more distinct, reflecting a \"High Segregation\" scenario.",
    "The surrogate model again successfully replicates these dynamics, while the ablation models continue to exhibit no structured behavior.",
    "Finally, Figure 10 demonstrates that, for ξ = ξ 3, the original ABM does not converge to a stable configuration.",
    "Instead, the high intolerance threshold causes agents to continuously relocate, preventing the emergence of segregated clusters."
